Former Manchester United midfielder, Paul Scholes, has given reasons why they lost 4-0 to Liverpool in the Premier League on Tuesday night. The Reds raced to a two-goal lead in the first half, thanks to Luis Diaz and Mohamed Salah. Sadio Mane and Salah scored after the break, as Jurgen Klopp’s men went top of the table. Scholes, speaking after the game, said: “There was a lack of fight in this team. “No quality in the squad. “I just worry about Manchester United. It’s as bad as I have seen it. “Where do you go from here? It’s embarrassing. “As a Manchester United player, you should come away from that game embarrassed.”